WEBVTT

00:01.268 --> 00:02.768
♪♪

00:02.770 --> 00:05.203
[grunts]

00:05.205 --> 00:06.605
Get--get over here!

00:06.607 --> 00:09.608
[grunts]

00:12.212 --> 00:13.678
Tents are lookin' good.

00:13.680 --> 00:15.514
And we made good time today.

00:15.516 --> 00:18.383
At this rate, we'll be at
Winsome Falls by tomorrow!

00:18.385 --> 00:20.452
We should do the annual big
sister little sister

00:20.454 --> 00:23.055
camping trip every weekend!

00:23.057 --> 00:25.090
Then it wouldn't be annual.

00:25.092 --> 00:26.591
And if we did it
every weekend,

00:26.593 --> 00:28.794
it probably wouldn't
be as special.

00:28.796 --> 00:32.064
But the more we do it, the
better we get at camping!

00:32.066 --> 00:33.565
Remember the first
time we came here

00:33.567 --> 00:35.734
and Rarity had that
gi-normous tent?

00:35.736 --> 00:36.768
I heard that!

00:36.770 --> 00:38.336
[giggle]

00:38.338 --> 00:40.606
I've gotten much better at
roughing it, haven't I?

00:42.176 --> 00:45.144
Yup. This time you only
packed three suitcases!

00:47.214 --> 00:49.481
I know what you're
thinking, but I promise...

00:49.483 --> 00:51.616
I only brought
the essentials.

00:51.618 --> 00:54.286
Like those light thingies?

00:54.288 --> 00:55.520
Of course!

00:55.522 --> 00:57.756
What is life if you
can't make it beautiful?

01:02.496 --> 01:05.597
Mmm. These berries look
good enough to eat.

01:06.667 --> 01:08.233
DON'T!

01:08.235 --> 01:10.636
According to my book, they're
extremely poisonous!

01:12.639 --> 01:13.705
[sigh]

01:18.112 --> 01:19.444
[scream]

01:19.446 --> 01:20.745
What!

01:20.747 --> 01:22.848
I heard something; I
stepped on something

01:22.850 --> 01:26.218
and I saw that
creepy cave.

01:26.220 --> 01:28.520
I guess I still get
a little bit scared
out here,

01:28.522 --> 01:30.655
even after the
last camping trip.

01:30.657 --> 01:34.726
Don't worry, kid, you've
got a big sister this time!

01:38.599 --> 01:40.866
Apple Bloom: This looks amazing!

01:40.868 --> 01:44.202
This is going to be the best
big sister/little sister

01:44.204 --> 01:45.771
camping trip ever!

01:52.146 --> 01:53.178
[splat]

01:54.381 --> 01:55.780
[buzzing]

01:55.782 --> 01:57.416
Aaaahhhhhh!

02:00.320 --> 02:04.222
<i>♪ My little pony,</i>
<i>my little pony ♪</i>

02:04.224 --> 02:06.158
<i>♪ Aaaahhh ♪</i>

02:06.160 --> 02:08.226
<i>♪ My little Pony ♪</i>

02:08.228 --> 02:10.262
<i>♪ I used to wonder what</i>
<i>friendship could be. ♪</i>

02:10.264 --> 02:11.930
<i>♪ My Little Pony ♪</i>

02:11.932 --> 02:14.533
<i>♪ Until you all shared</i>
<i>its magic with me. ♪</i>

02:14.535 --> 02:16.601
<i>♪ Big adventure! ♪</i>
<i>♪ Tons of fun ♪</i>

02:16.603 --> 02:18.770
<i>♪ A beautiful heart! ♪ ♪</i>
<i>Faithful and strong! ♪</i>

02:18.772 --> 02:20.906
<i>♪ Sharing kindness ♪</i>
<i>♪ it's an easy feat ♪</i>

02:20.908 --> 02:22.908
<i>♪ And magic makes it</i>
<i>all complete! ♪</i>

02:22.910 --> 02:25.243
<i>♪ To have my little pony ♪</i>

02:25.245 --> 02:28.547
<i>♪ Do you know you're all</i>
<i>my very best friends? ♪</i>

02:28.549 --> 02:31.150
♪♪

02:35.756 --> 02:38.790
[panicked chattering]

02:44.398 --> 02:47.832
Ow! What are these things?

02:47.834 --> 02:49.468
Fly-ders!

02:49.536 --> 02:51.503
Everypony run for cover!

02:51.505 --> 02:52.771
Don't get stuck
in their...

02:52.773 --> 02:53.638
[thud]

02:53.640 --> 02:54.673
web!

02:54.675 --> 02:56.208
[squealing]

02:56.210 --> 02:57.776
Agh! Now what?

02:57.778 --> 02:58.977
Follow me, everypony!

02:58.979 --> 03:04.316
♪♪

03:04.318 --> 03:05.584
Agh!

03:05.586 --> 03:07.452
Not the scary cave!

03:09.790 --> 03:11.656
[buzzing]

03:11.658 --> 03:14.226
Where did those
terrible bugs come from?

03:14.228 --> 03:16.394
And why did they
destroy our camp?

03:16.396 --> 03:18.563
Fly-ders are from
the Luna Bay Area.

03:18.565 --> 03:20.765
Never seen 'em this
far east though.

03:20.767 --> 03:22.667
Probably attracted
to the food.

03:22.669 --> 03:24.369
Best wait here
until they're gone.

03:24.371 --> 03:25.937
Oh, apple rot!

03:25.939 --> 03:28.240
What are we supposed to do now?

03:28.242 --> 03:30.909
We had games to play and
marshmallows to roast at camp!

03:30.911 --> 03:32.944
In here we got nothin'.

03:32.946 --> 03:35.480
That's not entirely true.

03:35.482 --> 03:37.249
We have each other.

03:37.251 --> 03:38.550
That's right.

03:38.552 --> 03:39.784
And if you girls want to,

03:39.786 --> 03:41.386
maybe we could tell some stories

03:41.388 --> 03:42.721
to pass the time.

03:42.723 --> 03:44.589
You want stories?

03:44.591 --> 03:46.625
I've got a ton of stories.

03:46.627 --> 03:50.929
Spoiler Alert: they're all
about me and how awesome I am.

03:50.931 --> 03:53.865
I was thinking more
like campfire stories.

03:53.867 --> 03:56.334
But we don't even
have a campfire.

03:56.336 --> 03:57.269
I got this!

03:59.573 --> 04:01.306
Wow. That was brave.

04:01.308 --> 04:04.476
Eh, it was no biggie.

04:04.478 --> 04:06.811
[cough]

04:06.813 --> 04:08.580
We aren't gonna
tell scary stories

04:08.582 --> 04:11.016
like our last camping
trip, are we?

04:11.018 --> 04:13.585
It's bad enough
just being in here.

04:13.587 --> 04:14.853
Don't worry, Scootaloo.

04:14.855 --> 04:18.423
I was gonna tell you mine and
Apple Bloom's favorite legend!

04:18.425 --> 04:20.292
Oh! You mean Rockhoof?

04:20.294 --> 04:21.726
I love that one!

04:21.728 --> 04:23.728
He was so strong and when he...

04:23.730 --> 04:25.664
Apple Bloom! Shhh. We
haven't heard it yet.

04:25.666 --> 04:26.931
Oh. OK.

04:26.933 --> 04:28.566
But it's so good!

04:28.568 --> 04:30.302
Well, it's true.

04:30.304 --> 04:33.638
Rockhoof was known far and wide
for his incredible strength

04:33.640 --> 04:35.707
but he didn't start
out that way.

04:35.709 --> 04:38.677
You see, Rockhoof was
a tiny little fella,

04:38.679 --> 04:39.678
the son of a farmer.

04:39.680 --> 04:40.645
Just like us!

04:40.647 --> 04:43.848
Heh heh heh.

04:43.850 --> 04:46.318
They lived in a village
that sat at the foot

04:46.320 --> 04:48.453
of a gigantic volcano.

04:48.455 --> 04:51.523
♪♪

04:51.525 --> 04:54.492
<i>And the village was protected by</i>
<i>an elite group of Guard Ponies</i>

04:54.494 --> 04:55.927
<i>called the Mighty Helm.</i>

04:55.929 --> 05:00.799
Ha ha ha ha!

05:00.801 --> 05:03.501
<i>Young Rockhoof wanted nothing</i>
<i>more than to be part</i>

05:03.503 --> 05:04.569
<i>of the Mighty Helm...</i>

05:08.842 --> 05:11.509
Ha ha ha ha ha!

05:11.511 --> 05:13.511
<i>but he was told that</i>
<i>he was too scrawny</i>

05:13.513 --> 05:15.013
<i>and weak to protect</i>
<i>the village.</i>

05:15.015 --> 05:20.585
[mocking laughter]

05:20.587 --> 05:22.020
[thud]

05:22.022 --> 05:25.623
<i>But Rockhoof wouldn't</i>
<i>take "no" for an answer.</i>

05:25.625 --> 05:29.661
♪♪

05:29.663 --> 05:32.764
<i>Then one fateful day...</i>

05:32.766 --> 05:34.966
<i>The volcano erupted!</i>

05:34.968 --> 05:37.001
[explosion]

05:37.003 --> 05:39.537
Eeeeeeeee!!

05:39.539 --> 05:41.039
This is my favorite part!

05:41.041 --> 05:42.541
What happened next?

05:44.478 --> 05:47.346
The molten lava poured down
the side of the volcano...

05:49.549 --> 05:52.117
<i>... and try as they might, the</i>
<i>Mighty Helm couldn't figure out</i>

05:52.119 --> 05:54.686
<i>a way to save the village.</i>

05:54.688 --> 05:56.821
<i>They had to evacuate.</i>

05:56.823 --> 05:58.890
<i>But the village ponies didn't</i>
<i>want to leave their homes!</i>

06:00.727 --> 06:02.694
<i>They spent their</i>
<i>entire lives there.</i>

06:02.696 --> 06:04.062
<i>They had nowhere else to go!</i>

06:08.135 --> 06:11.669
<i>So Rockhoof decided</i>
<i>to do something crazy.</i>

06:11.671 --> 06:16.941
♪♪

06:16.943 --> 06:19.677
<i>He thought if he could</i>
<i>divert the flow of the lava,</i>

06:19.679 --> 06:22.547
<i>he might be able to</i>
<i>save his village!</i>

06:22.549 --> 06:24.949
<i>He started digging a trench.</i>

06:24.951 --> 06:26.651
<i>Sweetie Belle: Wait a minute.</i>

06:26.653 --> 06:28.720
All by himself?

06:28.722 --> 06:32.023
It'd be impossible for one pony
to dig a trench fast enough

06:32.025 --> 06:33.758
to stop the lava!

06:33.760 --> 06:35.627
I mean, even I couldn't do that!

06:35.629 --> 06:37.862
[shriek]

06:37.864 --> 06:39.798
Good thing Rockhoof
didn't believe

06:39.800 --> 06:43.701
in the word "impossible".

06:43.703 --> 06:46.771
<i>He continued to work, knowing</i>
<i>the odds were against him</i>

06:46.773 --> 06:48.440
<i>but determined to push through.</i>

06:50.911 --> 06:53.845
<i>Then... something</i>
<i>magical happened.</i>

06:53.847 --> 06:58.783
♪♪

06:58.785 --> 07:02.020
<i>Rockhoof got visibly stronger!</i>

07:02.022 --> 07:03.822
<i>But the lava was</i>
<i>getting closer...</i>

07:03.824 --> 07:09.794
♪♪

07:09.796 --> 07:10.762
[crash]

07:19.172 --> 07:25.577
[cheers]

07:25.579 --> 07:28.046
<i>Through his extraordinary</i>
<i>determination</i>

07:28.048 --> 07:30.148
<i>and sheer force of will,</i>

07:30.150 --> 07:33.685
<i>Rockhoof more than earned</i>
<i>his place in the Mighty Helm.</i>

07:33.687 --> 07:35.820
[laughter]

07:35.822 --> 07:36.921
[whoops]

07:36.923 --> 07:37.989
Yeah!

07:37.991 --> 07:39.891
Good story,
Applejack!

07:39.893 --> 07:41.259
Even if it
wasn't about me.

07:41.261 --> 07:43.027
[giggles]

07:43.029 --> 07:46.264
I love that story, no matter
how many times I hear it.

07:46.266 --> 07:48.666
Why don't we see if it's
safe to head back to camp?

07:48.668 --> 07:50.802
Uh, girls?

07:50.804 --> 07:52.871
There is no camp to go back to.

07:52.873 --> 07:55.840
[buzzing]

07:55.842 --> 07:56.842
[gasps]

08:00.146 --> 08:04.115
♪♪

08:04.117 --> 08:06.251
All our hard work is ruined.

08:09.956 --> 08:11.222
There, there. Sweetie Belle.

08:11.224 --> 08:12.891
Not to worry.

08:12.893 --> 08:17.161
How? Our camp was so pretty and
this cave is sooo...

08:17.163 --> 08:19.163
not.

08:19.165 --> 08:21.900
Oh, nononono no, not true!

08:21.902 --> 08:23.735
There's beauty in everything.

08:23.737 --> 08:26.638
Even these blah rocks
aren't really blah!

08:26.640 --> 08:29.807
If you look closely, you can
see flecks of gold in them.

08:29.809 --> 08:32.744
And the way the firelight
dances on the cave wall...

08:32.746 --> 08:34.012
shadow and light!

08:34.014 --> 08:35.547
Ooooh, it's so gorgeous!

08:37.784 --> 08:41.953
Sweetie Belle, have I ever told
you about<i> my</i> favorite legend?

08:41.955 --> 08:44.255
No. I didn't know you had one.

08:44.257 --> 08:46.824
Her name was Mistmane.

08:46.826 --> 08:48.826
Mistmane?

08:48.828 --> 08:52.163
Isn't she the old wrinkly
sorceress with the flower?

08:52.165 --> 08:56.067
Yes. But did you
know she used to be

08:56.069 --> 08:59.871
the most beautiful
unicorn in all the land?

08:59.873 --> 09:01.639
No.

09:01.641 --> 09:03.608
So what happened to her?

09:03.610 --> 09:08.780
Well, Mistmane was a very
promising young sorceress.

09:08.782 --> 09:12.884
<i>She was as talented as she</i>
<i>was beautiful and kind.</i>

09:12.886 --> 09:15.019
<i>Everypony loved her</i>
<i>and missed her</i>

09:15.021 --> 09:17.188
<i>when she was sent to the</i>
<i>finest magic school.</i>

09:24.164 --> 09:26.965
<i>While she was gone, she was</i>
<i>delighted to find out</i>

09:26.967 --> 09:31.636
<i>that her best friend, Sable</i>
<i>Spirit, was crowned Empress.</i>

09:31.638 --> 09:35.607
<i>She couldn't wait to return home</i>
<i>once she finished her studies.</i>

09:35.609 --> 09:39.777
<i>But once she arrived, she was</i>
<i>devastated by what she saw.</i>

09:39.779 --> 09:44.983
♪♪

09:44.985 --> 09:46.851
What happened here?

09:46.853 --> 09:49.020
The Empress happened.

09:49.022 --> 09:52.323
She makes everypony work
day and night on her palace.

09:52.325 --> 09:54.826
We don't have time to take
care of anything else.

09:54.828 --> 09:55.893
Well, that can't be.

09:55.895 --> 09:57.362
I know her.

09:57.364 --> 10:00.131
She would never do this.

10:00.133 --> 10:02.968
<i>But there was no denying</i>
<i>what was in front of her.</i>

10:10.710 --> 10:13.011
<i>Sable Spirit took everything</i>
<i>that was beautiful</i>

10:13.013 --> 10:15.747
<i>away from anypony else.</i>

10:15.749 --> 10:19.150
<i>But Mistmane was sure there</i>
<i>had to be some explanation.</i>

10:21.054 --> 10:23.655
I'd assume there was
too, if somepony told me

10:23.657 --> 10:25.857
either one of you
two'd gone evil.

10:25.859 --> 10:27.792
Yeah, I'd never believe it.

10:27.794 --> 10:29.227
I dunno.

10:29.229 --> 10:32.130
I've seen the way you two
get when you miss breakfast.

10:32.132 --> 10:33.831
Ha! Just kidding!

10:33.833 --> 10:35.400
But I'd want answers, too.

10:35.402 --> 10:37.335
So did Mistmane.

10:37.337 --> 10:39.337
She went to confront her friend.

10:39.339 --> 10:44.709
♪♪

10:44.711 --> 10:47.011
Sable? Is that you?

10:47.013 --> 10:50.415
Don't tell me you don't
recognize your old friend.

10:50.417 --> 10:53.685
I don't. My friend would never
work our families and friends

10:53.687 --> 10:56.454
to the bone for something
as silly as a palace.

10:56.456 --> 11:00.391
Silly? My palace is
a beacon of beauty.

11:00.393 --> 11:04.696
Anypony who passes will
be in awe of its majesty.

11:04.698 --> 11:07.899
What good is a pretty palace if
it just hides the misery

11:07.901 --> 11:09.400
of its ponies?

11:09.402 --> 11:11.803
Beauty is everything.

11:11.805 --> 11:13.471
You taught me that.

11:13.473 --> 11:14.939
What?

11:14.941 --> 11:16.741
You were always
the pretty one.

11:16.743 --> 11:19.043
You got to go to the
best magic school.

11:19.045 --> 11:20.878
Everypony missed you.

11:20.880 --> 11:22.814
Everypony loved you.

11:22.816 --> 11:25.083
I admit, I was jealous.

11:25.085 --> 11:29.787
So I tried to perform a spell
that would make me beautiful.

11:29.789 --> 11:31.956
You can see how<i> that</i> went.

11:31.958 --> 11:33.458
[gasp]

11:33.460 --> 11:36.861
I vowed if I couldn't have
beauty, I would take it.

11:36.863 --> 11:39.263
I wasn't chosen to
be Empress, you know.

11:39.265 --> 11:41.099
I took it.

11:41.101 --> 11:45.269
Just like I'm going to
take everything else.

11:45.271 --> 11:47.271
Mistmane: I can't
let you do that.

11:47.273 --> 11:52.176
Let me? [laughter]

11:52.178 --> 11:55.246
[zapping]

11:55.248 --> 11:58.283
♪♪

12:03.923 --> 12:05.290
[screech]

12:07.527 --> 12:09.827
[whoosh]

12:09.829 --> 12:14.499
<i>♪ [dramatic music] ♪</i>

12:14.501 --> 12:17.335
<i>♪♪</i>

12:24.310 --> 12:25.443
Agh!

12:25.445 --> 12:27.245
♪♪

12:28.481 --> 12:30.515
[cheers]

12:30.517 --> 12:33.017
<i>Rarity: Everypony thought</i>
<i>Sable Spirit was defeated</i>

12:33.019 --> 12:34.852
<i>and that was that.</i>

12:34.854 --> 12:37.856
<i>But Mistmane knew there was</i>
<i>more she could do to help.</i>

12:40.493 --> 12:43.861
<i>Beauty isn't everything, but</i>
<i>Mistmane knew that it does have</i>

12:43.863 --> 12:45.997
<i>the power to make ponies smile.</i>

12:45.999 --> 12:50.935
♪♪

12:50.937 --> 12:53.471
<i>She made a huge sacrifice to</i>
<i>bring that smile back</i>

12:53.473 --> 12:55.573
<i>to her friends' and</i>
<i>families' faces.</i>

12:55.575 --> 12:57.809
♪♪

12:57.811 --> 12:59.544
<i>Including Sable Spirit's.</i>

13:05.552 --> 13:07.485
You did this for me?

13:07.487 --> 13:11.422
Even after I was so cruel?

13:11.424 --> 13:13.591
<i>Sable Spirit was so touched</i>

13:13.593 --> 13:15.393
<i>that she vowed to be</i>
<i>more like her friend</i>

13:15.395 --> 13:17.195
<i>in the ways that mattered.</i>

13:17.197 --> 13:20.431
<i>From then on, she ruled with</i>
<i>kindness and compassion.</i>

13:26.940 --> 13:30.108
[cheers]

13:33.046 --> 13:35.513
<i>Even though she gave</i>
<i>away her physical beauty,</i>

13:35.515 --> 13:37.615
<i>she dedicated her life to</i>
<i>spreading beauty</i>

13:37.617 --> 13:41.452
<i>all over Equestria.</i>

13:41.454 --> 13:44.288
<i>Anytime you go out of your way</i>
<i>to brighten somepony's day</i>

13:44.290 --> 13:47.024
<i>by doing something nice</i>
<i>like giving them flowers,</i>

13:47.026 --> 13:49.427
you're following in the
hoofsteps of Mistmane.

13:52.632 --> 13:55.266
I think she's my
favorite legend, too.

13:56.970 --> 13:58.269
[hiss]

13:59.572 --> 14:02.506
Ahhh!!!!

14:02.508 --> 14:04.242
Ugh!

14:04.244 --> 14:06.210
These Fly-ders won't quit!

14:06.212 --> 14:08.112
What do they want from us now?

14:08.114 --> 14:11.315
Well, like it or
not, we're food too.

14:11.317 --> 14:13.251
And I've got the
bites to prove it!

14:13.253 --> 14:14.485
What are we going to do?

14:14.487 --> 14:15.620
They're almost here!

14:16.956 --> 14:18.923
[crashing]

14:22.262 --> 14:23.294
What?

14:23.296 --> 14:25.096
Now those bugs can't get in.

14:26.232 --> 14:27.498
[panicked gasps]

14:27.500 --> 14:29.533
And<i> we</i> can't get<i> out</i> !

14:29.535 --> 14:30.434
Ah!

14:30.436 --> 14:31.569
[panting]

14:34.941 --> 14:37.408
[panting]

14:37.410 --> 14:39.510
Let's all just stay calm.

14:39.512 --> 14:41.212
Lemme re-light this fire.

14:42.548 --> 14:44.548
[whoosh]

14:44.550 --> 14:47.151
We just have to wait
until the swarm moves on.

14:47.153 --> 14:48.519
Then we'll think of a way out.

14:48.521 --> 14:50.154
How long will
that be?

14:50.156 --> 14:51.522
Don't bears live in caves?

14:53.960 --> 14:55.459
Whoa, whoa.

14:55.461 --> 14:57.495
Scootaloo, you're focusing
on the wrong things.

14:57.497 --> 14:58.562
You have a plan?

14:58.564 --> 14:59.630
Close.

14:59.632 --> 15:02.199
I have a story!

15:02.201 --> 15:04.502
Let me guess,
it's about you?

15:04.504 --> 15:06.404
Practically.

15:06.406 --> 15:10.474
It's about<i> my</i> favorite
legend, Flash Magnus.

15:10.476 --> 15:12.977
Wasn't he the pony who
took on the Dragons?

15:12.979 --> 15:14.211
Dragons?

15:14.213 --> 15:16.614
Big, scary mean
ones or like Spike?

15:16.616 --> 15:20.351
Oh, these were definitely
the big scary mean kind.

15:23.556 --> 15:26.057
But not too scary.

15:26.059 --> 15:27.592
You can sit closer
to me if you want.

15:30.129 --> 15:34.999
A long time ago, before the
Wonderbolts were even founded,

15:35.001 --> 15:38.303
Flash Magnus was a lowly
cadet in the Royal Legion.

15:44.377 --> 15:47.244
And the Legion needed to
fly over the Dragon Lands

15:47.246 --> 15:50.081
to get to their comrades
on the other side.

15:50.083 --> 15:52.216
But as they got closer
to the Dragons...

15:52.218 --> 15:53.617
[growl]

15:53.619 --> 15:55.720
... The Dragons attacked!

15:55.722 --> 15:58.322
You said this wasn't too scary!

15:58.324 --> 16:00.191
[muffled] Scootaloo, if you
just hang in there...

16:00.193 --> 16:01.125
What?

16:03.062 --> 16:06.063
I said, if you
just hang in there,

16:06.065 --> 16:08.299
I promise you'll
like the ending.

16:08.301 --> 16:11.502
So, like I way saying, Flash
Magnus and the Royal Legion

16:11.504 --> 16:15.006
tried to get past the dragons...

16:15.008 --> 16:16.507
<i>... but the Dragons</i>
<i>wouldn't let them.</i>

16:18.711 --> 16:21.646
Everypony, RETREAT!

16:25.084 --> 16:27.318
<i>Flash Magnus and a few other</i>
<i>cadets were separated</i>

16:27.320 --> 16:28.453
<i>from the battalion.</i>

16:31.791 --> 16:34.792
<i>He managed to get away but the</i>
<i>dragons captured his friends</i>

16:34.794 --> 16:36.194
<i>and took them back</i>
<i>to their lair.</i>

16:37.263 --> 16:38.196
[scream]

16:40.066 --> 16:43.101
♪♪

16:51.778 --> 16:53.077
Commander!

16:53.079 --> 16:55.146
We need to save our
captured comrades.

16:55.148 --> 16:57.581
I appreciate your
loyalty, Flash Magnus,

16:57.583 --> 17:00.418
but getting past those dragons
is going to be impossible!

17:00.420 --> 17:01.452
Nothing will work.

17:03.656 --> 17:05.322
<i>The Commander was right.</i>

17:05.324 --> 17:07.425
You can't
out-fight Dragons.

17:07.427 --> 17:09.794
But you can out-think them.

17:14.133 --> 17:18.269
Commander Ironhead, I'm pretty
sure I can out-fly the Dragons.

17:18.271 --> 17:20.171
If I can lure them
into chasing me,

17:20.173 --> 17:22.239
you can all sneak into the
lair and retrieve our friends

17:22.241 --> 17:24.508
before they get back.

17:24.510 --> 17:27.812
Are you really willing to
take that chance, Soldier?

17:27.814 --> 17:29.347
I am, Sir.

17:31.150 --> 17:33.484
It's a very brave
thing you're doing.

17:33.486 --> 17:35.153
You'll need all the
help you can get.

17:38.724 --> 17:40.825
Is this... Netitus?

17:40.827 --> 17:43.394
The fireproof shield?

17:43.396 --> 17:46.130
It has protected legion
heroes for generations

17:46.132 --> 17:48.833
and today I can't think
of a worthier flank

17:48.835 --> 17:50.435
for Netitus to protect!

17:51.671 --> 17:53.404
Good luck, soldier.

17:53.406 --> 17:55.773
<i>♪ [military theme] ♪</i>

17:55.775 --> 17:59.443
♪♪

17:59.445 --> 18:03.514
Hey! Come and get me,
fire breath! If you can!

18:03.516 --> 18:05.449
Hey! Hey! Come and get me!

18:05.451 --> 18:06.451
Hey! I'm over here!

18:08.287 --> 18:09.453
[whoosh]

18:13.159 --> 18:15.860
<i>While Flash Magnus</i>
<i>bravely flew for his life,</i>

18:15.862 --> 18:18.596
<i>Commander Ironhead was able</i>
<i>to get his soldiers back.</i>

18:18.598 --> 18:22.900
♪♪

18:22.902 --> 18:24.635
<i>Flash Magnus flew like the wind.</i>

18:24.637 --> 18:27.905
[whoosh]

18:27.907 --> 18:29.507
<i>Faster than the dragons!</i>

18:29.509 --> 18:34.845
<i>♪♪</i>

18:34.847 --> 18:37.315
<i>But he knew he couldn't</i>
<i>do this forever.</i>

18:38.918 --> 18:41.752
<i>Luckily, he had a plan.</i>

18:41.754 --> 18:43.220
[thunderclap]

18:43.222 --> 18:46.924
♪♪

18:46.926 --> 18:48.225
[whistle]

18:48.227 --> 18:51.328
♪♪

18:51.330 --> 18:53.864
[whoosh]

18:53.866 --> 18:56.367
<i>He led the dragons</i>
<i>straight into a storm</i>

18:56.369 --> 18:57.735
<i>that the Legion had planted.</i>

18:57.737 --> 19:00.771
[thunderclap]

19:00.773 --> 19:03.841
<i>One taste of the lightning</i>
<i>and the dragons retreated!</i>

19:12.318 --> 19:13.584
[cough]

19:13.586 --> 19:16.187
<i>Flash Magnus' plan worked!</i>

19:16.189 --> 19:17.955
[cheers]

19:17.957 --> 19:21.192
♪♪

19:26.899 --> 19:27.965
Wow!

19:27.967 --> 19:29.366
I did like that ending.

19:29.368 --> 19:30.868
Told ya!

19:30.870 --> 19:34.471
He always inspired me to be
my brave and awesome self.

19:34.473 --> 19:35.739
Mmhmm!

19:35.741 --> 19:38.542
Yeah, I guess he kinda
reminds me of you.

19:38.544 --> 19:39.677
You guess?

19:39.679 --> 19:40.744
Come on!

19:40.746 --> 19:42.513
I'm just like him.

19:42.515 --> 19:44.949
[laughter]

19:46.719 --> 19:47.952
Hey, d'you hear that?

19:49.555 --> 19:51.422
I don't hear anything.

19:51.424 --> 19:52.656
Exactly.

19:52.658 --> 19:54.858
Those gosh darn
fly-ders are gone!

19:54.860 --> 19:55.860
We can get out!

19:58.364 --> 19:59.397
Whoa!

20:00.566 --> 20:02.266
Or not.

20:02.268 --> 20:04.702
We're gonna have to see if we
can get out the other way.

20:05.738 --> 20:09.273
You mean go further into
the dark, spooky cave?

20:09.275 --> 20:12.243
Scootaloo, just
remember the story.

20:12.245 --> 20:15.512
You've gotta be brave like
me and Flash Magnus. OK?

20:15.514 --> 20:20.951
♪♪

20:20.953 --> 20:22.519
I hear water!

20:22.521 --> 20:24.355
And if there's
flowing water, then...

20:24.357 --> 20:26.323
It might lead to the way out!

20:26.325 --> 20:28.525
Ohhh!

20:28.527 --> 20:30.694
OK on three!

20:30.696 --> 20:31.662
One.

20:31.664 --> 20:32.630
Two.

20:32.632 --> 20:33.564
THREE!

20:33.566 --> 20:36.434
[splashes]

20:39.272 --> 20:40.037
Woohoo!

20:40.039 --> 20:41.472
Yeah!

20:41.474 --> 20:45.509
♪♪

20:45.511 --> 20:47.344
Well, whaddaya know?

20:47.346 --> 20:50.547
We found ourselves a
shortcut to Winsome Falls!

20:50.549 --> 20:53.884
Scootaloo: It's never
looked so beautiful!

20:53.886 --> 20:55.519
Well, almost...

20:59.992 --> 21:01.759
We sure are sorry
that our camping trip

21:01.761 --> 21:03.327
wasn't what we
hoped it would be.

21:03.329 --> 21:04.361
Are you kidding?

21:04.363 --> 21:06.797
This trip is awesome!

21:06.799 --> 21:08.465
It is?

21:08.467 --> 21:12.036
We got to hear legendary stories
and go on an adventure.

21:12.038 --> 21:14.505
Wait, you three want to stay?

21:14.507 --> 21:17.308
Of course we do!

21:17.310 --> 21:20.544
We could turn those trees
into a nice little shelter.

21:20.546 --> 21:23.480
We can get you some big logs
and branches to help build it.

21:23.482 --> 21:25.582
And I bet we can find
some more berries.

21:25.584 --> 21:27.651
Come on!

21:27.653 --> 21:30.021
I can't wait to see
what happens next year!

21:34.026 --> 21:36.060
<i>♪ My Little Pony ♪</i>

21:38.531 --> 21:40.564
<i>♪ My Little Pony ♪</i>

21:51.410 --> 21:53.711
<i>♪ My Little Pony ♪</i>

21:53.713 --> 21:57.748
<i>♪ friends ♪</i>
